//Keratin - what you understand by it?
It's a natural type of protein found in your hair, nails & skin.
In a Keratin treatment, Protein is artificially added to your hair to make it look smooth, shiny and frizz-free! Kindly note it's just a coating on each hair strand, and does not touch your scalp.

During the treatment, the product is applied on fresh hair, left to penetrate for 30/40 mins and then ironed to seal in the product ( during that process, eyes do get watery😉 ) followed by a wash (Brasil Cacau Keratin Treatment is the one I am talking about here)
• Is Keratin good for your hair?
Yes, because your hair becomes healthier and stronger.

• How long does the treatment last? 
Approx 2 - 3 months depending on your after care.

• Is it safe to do this treatment?
Yes, it is but provided you use the right brand. All Keratin products have a harmful chemical Formaldehyde, so always ask the salon for its percentage in the brand that will be used on you.

• Can it be done on chemical treated or coloured hair? 
Yes, works well on both.

• How long does it take for the treatment?
Approximately 3 to 4 hours depending on your hair length ( My hair length takes 5 hours🙄 )

• Does it cause hairfall?
Though there is information stating that it does in some cases, but honestly it hasn't done that to my hair ever. (I have been doing Keratin for almost 6 years now)

• How expensive it the treatment?
It starts from Rs.5k onwards approximately depending on the hair length (Ahmedabad rates)
(it's just an approximate rate which will vary city, brand, salon & hair lengthwise)

However, kindly note Keratin is a Chemical treatment and needs proper after care too. Thus, consult and understand the whole treatment completely with your Stylist before indulging into it, as above is completely my perspective.

For years, I get my hair treatments done only in Ahmedabad and blindly trust Sneha Acharya @acharyasneha, the hair connoisseur, with my tresses. 
Bring life and shine back to your lifeless hair with - Keratin Protein Treatment.

P.S. This is not a Paid or Sponsored post!
